# Cursor IDE Configuration for MCP Context7

## MCP Server Configuration
The project uses Model Context Protocol (MCP) with Context7 server for enhanced AI assistance.

### MCP Context7 Setup
- **Server**: Context7 MCP server
- **Protocol**: Model Context Protocol v1.0
- **Integration**: Backend API endpoints at `/api/mcp/*`

### Key Features
- User context management
- Contextual recommendations
- Real-time context updates
- AI-powered insights

### Development Guidelines
- Always check MCP server status before operations
- Use proper error handling for MCP calls
- Implement context validation
- Follow MCP protocol standards

### API Endpoints
- `POST /api/mcp/initialize` - Initialize MCP server
- `GET /api/mcp/status` - Check server status
- `GET /api/mcp/context/:userId` - Get user context
- `PUT /api/mcp/context/:userId` - Update user context
- `GET /api/mcp/recommendations/:userId` - Get recommendations

### Environment Variables
- `CONTEXT7_API_KEY` - Your Context7 API key
- `CONTEXT7_BASE_URL` - Context7 API base URL

### Testing
- Test MCP endpoints before deployment
- Verify context data integrity
- Check server connectivity
